-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_returns.sql
-- Deduplicate multiple return submissions per item; pick one approved return per item
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        return_id,
        item_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY
                CASE WHEN status = 'approved' THEN 0 ELSE 1 END ASC,
                return_date DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
)
SELECT
    item_id,
    return_id,
    return_date,
    reason,
    status
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1 AND status = 'approved'
```

```sql
-- models/intermediate/int_items_with_returns.sql
-- Join order items with returns to identify returned items
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        oi.item_id,
        oi.product_id,
        CASE WHEN r.item_id IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS is_returned
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} r
        ON r.item_id = oi.item_id
)
SELECT
    item_id,
    product_id,
    is_returned
FROM source
```

-- models/intermediate/int_products_with_categories.sql
-- Join products with categories, handling missing category values
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        p.product_id,
        p.name,
        COALESCE(c.category_id, -1) AS category_id,
        COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)') AS category_name
    FROM {{ ref('stg_products') }} p
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
        ON c.category_id = p.category_id
)
SELECT
    product_id,
    name,
    category_id,
    category_name
FROM source
```

```sql
-- models/mart/fct_return_rate_by_category.sql
-- Calculate product return rates by category
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        pc.category_name,
        ir.is_returned
    FROM {{ ref('int_items_with_returns') }} ir
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_products_with_categories') }} pc
        ON pc.product_id = ir.product_id
)
SELECT
    category_name,
    COUNT(*) AS total_items_sold,
    SUM(is_returned) AS total_items_returned,
    ROUND(SUM(is_returned)::NUMERIC / COUNT(*), 4) AS return_rate
FROM source
GROUP BY category_name
ORDER BY category_name
